                       gridspec_kw={'height_ratios':[1,2]}) 

# use this to squeeze the 2 subplots super close to cover the category labels
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.01) 
plt.title('MaSp1:MaSp2 in Major',y=1.55)
#sns.despine(bottom=True)
sns.boxplot(x='Diet',y='MaSp1:MaSp2',data=all_genes,ax=axes[0], palette='Paired')

axes[0].set_ylim(6,7.1)
axes[0].set_ylabel('')
axes[0].tick_params(labelsize=15)

#sns.despine(fig=None, ax=None, top=True, right=True, left=False, bottom=False, offset=None, trim=False)

a=sns.boxplot(x='Diet',y='MaSp1:MaSp2',data=all_genes,ax=axes[1])
axes[1].set_ylim(0,2.4)
axes[1].set_ylabel('')
axes[1].set_xlabel('')
t= axes[1].text(-0.07,0.95,'==',size=14,ha='left',transform=axes[1].transAxes)
t.set_bbox(dict(facecolor='white',edgecolor='white'))
#plt.savefig('SA_MaSp1 to MaSp2 in Major.png') # SA for split axis

a.tick_params(labelsize=15)
a.axes.set_title('MaSp1 to MaSp2 in major', fontsize=18)

png1.close()
